result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jean R Sirek in court with attorney Chris M. Lummis. Cass W Cousins appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Cases heard today are 15CT319, 15TR2703, 15TR3065 & 16CM74

8:33 a.m. Court calls the case. Atty Cousins states appearances.

Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed.
Prosecutor states plea agreement.
Attorney for Defendant concurs with agreement stated.

Defendant enters a plea of: 
15CT319
Count 1: No Contest

Court questions Defendant regarding plea.
Court informs Defendant of Constitutional Rights. Court advises Defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge.
Court questions Attorney for Defendant.
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge(s).

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge(s).
Court finds the defendant guilty of 15CT319 Count 1.  Clerk directed to enter Judgment of Conviction this date.
15CT319 Count 2 is dismissed. 
15TR3065 is dismissed and read-in. 
16CM74 is dismissed and read-in. 
15TR2703 is not reasonable.

Atty Cousins makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Atty Lummis makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Defendant makes statements to the Court.
Atty Cousins makes rebuttal statements.

BY THE COURT:
15CT319
Count 1
75 days jail starts today, last 1/2 of sentence to be served on electonic monitor, if defendant qualifies.
1 Day jail credit
$2,502 fine 
26.45 blood draw fee
60 days to pay or setup a payment plan today.
31 months drivers license revocation
31 months IID
AODA & comply with treatment recommendations. 

9:27 a.m. Court is back on the record. Atty. Lummis  in court for defendant. Atty. Cousins in case for the state.

Court has been informed huber was missed, DNA surcharge was missed, and DNA sample.

BY THE COURT:
Huber is granted, if the jail allows.
DNA Surcharge is added to fine.
Submit DNA sample.
Plea hearing on September 12, 2016 at 08:30 am.
Status conference on September 14, 2016 at 08:30 am.
Status conference on September 15, 2016 at 08:30 am.
Pre-trial conference on March 28, 2016 at 09:30 am.
Comply with all other bonds including 15CT319.

Defendant Jean R Sirek in court with attorney Chris M. Lummis. David R. Knaapen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  
Attorney/Defendant received copy of criminal complaint.

Attorney/Defendant waives reading of complaint.

NOT GUILTY plea entered.
